11/29/2023

Crime statistics data set for the City of Houston

  • In this project I processed data set of 2022 crime statistics for the City of Houston. The data set is posted in the City of Houston Official website
  • The NIBRS Data is updated monthly in one aggregated Excel spreadsheet, NIBRS stands for National Incident-Based Reporting System
  • the data on the Excel spread sheet only shows the police calls that resulted in filing a report, keep in mind that most police calls doesn’t warrant a police report for example Alarm calls, traffic stops, trespassers, disturbances.
  • This data does not account for unreported crimes in the City of Houston.
  • The data shows incident numbers and organized by Zip codes, Police Districts and Beats, street and block numbers.

Data dictionary

  • the data contains 249912 rows and 16 variables.
  • Occurrence Date: date of the incident.
  • Occurrence Hour: hour when the incident occurred, recorded in military time.
  • NIBRS Description: offense type.
  • Offense Count: number of offenses committed.
  • Beat: beat where the incident occurred.
  • Premise : location type where the incident occurred.
  • Block Range: street block number where the incident occurred.
  • Street Name: street name where the incident occurred.
  • Street Type: street type (Dr, St, Ave)
  • Suffix [Streets]: N, S, W, E.

Beats and districts

  • Police departments don’t respond to calls by Zip codes. they respond to calls by districts and beats.

  • The city is divided to districts and each district is divided to beats.

  • Beat is the area that’s being patrolled

  • Districts are divided between police stations throughout the city.

  • Pdf file of districts and beats was obtained from the city of Houston website

  • The next slide display the city of Houston map per district and beat

  • I patrolled 18 district from 2018 until 2021

  • I investigate robbery cases in 1,2,9,10, and 17 districts

Conclusion

  • from data analysis conducted on this data set I observed the following:
  • 77036 Zip Codes has the highest rate of reported crimes
  • 18 district has the highest incidents in the City of Houston
  • Hour of the day that have highest incident is between 1200-1300
  • Number of Homicides is 411 with 14 district having the highest murders rate (41), and Zip code 77036 having the highest murder rate (21) per zip code
  • Murder incidents have the highest distribution per month in June
  • Robberies incident have the highest distribution per month in January
  • Residential properties account for most of the reported incidents
